title: prevent resulting src="" in html
body: Hello, Current implementation of ngSrc may lead to empty src attribute when page is loading. For example: ``` ``` can be temporarily rendered as ``` ``` before the ```image``` resource is loaded. Some browser emits a request to *the current page* when seeing `````` (Firefox13 and IE8 will, Chromium20 won't), which leads to performance problems. This commit addressed this issue.

title: Issue #856: add ability to reset a form to its pristine state
body:
This is a fix for the (quite up-voted now) issue #856. The whole commit boils down to adding the $setPristine() method to both ng.directive:form.FormController and ng.directive:ngModel.NgModelController; tests are added as well.

Here is a jsFiddle that shows an issue: http://jsfiddle.net/pkozlowski_opensource/qT9pu/2/ (just type sth in a field and then delete it).

Here is another jsFillde with the issue fixed: http://jsfiddle.net/pkozlowski_opensource/2x8HD/4/ (just type sth in a field and then delete it and click on 'Revert edits').

body:
First change for https://github.com/angular/angular.js/issues/1041

Changes include:

title: fix($http): lowercase keys of headers when headers is an object.
body: Can't get header value because the keys are not lowercased. I guess this is a bug.

title: Appends slashes to urls
body: Angular intenionally removes slashes from urls defined in ngResource and this causes bugs and problems in frameworks like django. It simply *adds* slashes to urls for it work.

title: Typo on ng.$routeProvider docs
body: Just a minor typo: it says "`$aftreRouteChange`" where it meant `$afterRouteChange`.

title: fix($location): url rewriting if element was removed
body:
When user clicks a link, $location needs to intercept this event.  The <a> doesn't have to be target element of the DOM event, so it needs to traverse the DOM, to find first <a> parent.

If the target element was removed from DOM, during the same event, it would throw an exception. This fixes the issue.

Closes #1058

title: Fixed booleanAttrs to sync model.
body:

Using link instead of compile to fix this issue.
